title: For Sale:  Juch Ferlach highly ornate custom left hand 30-06
postcontent: Here is an extremely rare, high quality custom rifle built by Ferlach in Austria. This rife was custom built for an Army officer stationed in Germany in the early 90's. It is a highly ornate, extremely rare rifle in the US. The action of course is a commercial right hand Mauser and the stock is fitted for a left hand shooter with left hand cheek piece. The stock has a fitted "Old English" rubber butt pad. THe stock is a light colored, nicely figured, European walnut. It has typical narrow style european sling swivels. Beautifully stepped and sculpted European cheek piece on the right side of the stock for LEFT HANDED USE. The pistol grip has a rosewood fitting with personalized, engraved center device. The checkering uses an oak leaf border motif with fish scale checkering on both sides. The same checkering style matches the beautifully tapered forearm. There are a few light scuffs and small dings in the stock but overall it is in excellent condition. The action is a pleasing grey finish with a Edelweiss motif on the front and back receiver bridges as well as the highly ornate floor plate. This rifle was obviously built for mountain hunting so the decorative styling matches. The barrel is a full tapered octagon with a matte rib and iron. sights. The blue is perfect from end to end and the bore is bright and shiny. The rifle was built with claw mounts and a factory fitted high quality Swarovski 6X scope with 42MM objective. As you might expect it has the typical German crosshair. The rifle with scope tips the scales at 8.5lbs exactly. This is an unbelievably beautiful and functional rifle. if you are a lefty and want the very best this is for you. If you just love high quality custom rifles and want to own a functional work of art this is for you!

Allen Company Archery Broadhead Wrench ($2.49) CONDITION:I replaced the rear collapsible grip on the crossbow with a fixed one due to the handle rattling when operating (the major complaint with this model was alerting animals with the rattle from the collapsible grip).  The rubber on the rear bolt guide grip (forgive me for not knowing the exact name of this piece) has a small tear where the nock of a crossbolt caught it sliding in.  The broadheads have never been shot.  The shooting bock has maybe 20 shots in it total and still has an extremely long life left in it.COMMENTS:  This crossbow really is a beast.  I've shown quite a few of my hunting friends who have said their crossbows are nothing like it and lack in the raw power that this thing puts out.  While I love the idea of keeping this thing around in the event I would use it, bottom line is that it's just sitting in my collection and seeing no action.  I purchased everything in this listing brand-new for more than the current $1,064 list price for all of it.  The crossbow has maybe 25 shots through it in total, no mechanical malfunctions, and works like a charm!  To see s more detailed description, you can copy the names of the items and search for them on Amazon.com (this is where also where I pulled current pricing from).

title: For Sale:  WTS - Fostech Echo Trigger - NIB
postcontent: For sale is a Brand New In Box, Fostech Echo Trigger.  Comes with three position trigger (Safe, Semi, Echo) and bolt carrier group. The Echo is unique to any other pull/release trigger in that it has an integrated disconnector ("trigger lock"), much like a machine gun. This allows for high rates of fire (700-900 rounds per minute) with no hammer follow and utmost reliability. It's quite literally the closest thing to a machine gun this side of the NFA.  Item Description: This trigger is designed with safety being of the utmost priority. When the operator is in the Echo Mode of operation and depresses the trigger one round is fired. The operator can move the safety selector to the safe or semi-automatic mode and a second round will NOT fire upon release of the trigger. This is a Drop-in design and comes with a stripped carrier with gas key & ambidextrous safety selector. This trigger has 3 MODES OF OPERATION: 1. SAFE MODE: Firearm will NOT fire. 2. SEMI MODE: Firearm fires when trigger is pulled. 3. ECHO MODE : Firearm fires when trigger is pulled and also fires when trigger is released. ATF Approved! Comes in unopened packaging and original shipping box.Here's an opportunity to get one before Christmas - $625 Shipped (Price Reflects Current 9 Month Backorder). title: For Sale:  380 ACP  “Afforadable Protection”  Hi Point
postcontent:
Brand: Hi Point
Caliber:   380 ACP
Original Factory Box includedAffordable protection made in the USA ..... that’s a Hi Point. One the best values for the money!
 
How can a manufacturer make a gun in the United States for such a low price? Simple design, easy manufacture, and inexpensive materials.   A Hi Point is elegant in its design simplicity. They’re blowback-operated, so there is no “lock up” to get compromised by a glob of mud.  Mechanically, there’s just not that much that can break. Read some of the reports on the testing of this gun. 
 
This gun relies on the weight of the slide to keep the gun closed during firing. When the slide is closed, it simply sits against the back of the cartridge when it goes off.  The slide moves backward from the blowback pressure of the cartridge, and is returned forward by a return spring.  The barrel is pinned to the frame so it doesn’t even move.  So as long as the slide can move backward and fully forward, a Hi Point cycles.   It won’t win a beauty contest, but it works!
 
The Hi Point warranty covers damage and normal wear and tear with no questions asked.  If it breaks for any reason—EVER–Hi Point will repair or replace the gun free for the life of the gun no matter if you’re the original owner or not.
